         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">28/3/69 ¶  ¶ I am glad, dear Mr Bentham, to receive already the 30 copies of vol IV, which have been distributed by the Government to public institutions, ministers of the Crown and the few principle ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">69.03.28c</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1858-70, f. 375.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">28/3/69</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am glad, dear Mr Bentham, to receive already the 30 copies of vol IV, which have been distributed by the Government to public institutions, ministers of the Crown and the few principle contributors here in Australia to the work.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You will receive by the Anglesey 2 large cases, with the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">rest</hi>
               </seg> of <name key="Dicotyledoneae">Dicotyledoneae</name>. Before the next volume will be printed there will however be some supplemental collections, I suppose, from various sources.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <name key="Maireana">Maireana</name> must certainly be united with one of Lindley's Kochias, as I will show in my notes on <name key="Salsolaceae">Salsolaceae</name>.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">B69.06.03, pp. 8-15, at p. 12.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> Indeed all Australian Kochias (inclusive of Browns K. aphylla)<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>R. Brown (1810), p. 409.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> would be <name key="Maireana">Maireana</name>s except K. brevifolia. The character of the entirety of the fruit wing is however trifling and not even absolute.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Trusting you are well I remain</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your regardful </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The index of the 6 vol of the Fragmenta will now at last be printed. Meanwhile I have a good deal of manuscript ready for vol. VII.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The <name key="Monocotyledoneae">Monocotyledoneae</name> will now be attacked, and <name key="Xerotes">Xerotes</name> first of all, as I have a good deal done for years to get new diagnoses of all the species.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">B74.08.01, pp. 205-14.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Dicotyledoneae">Dicotyledoneae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Kochia%20aphylla">Kochia aphylla</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Kochia%20brevifolia">Kochia brevifolia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Maireana">Maireana</name>
            </p>
